instruction: Conduct a regression analysis with the five style-factor variables and compare the explanatory power to baseline regressions using only traditional U.K. property-type/geography segmentations.
output: After conducting the regression analysis with the five style-factor variables, we found that the explanatory power improved significantly compared to the baseline regressions that only used traditional U.K. property-type/geography segmentations. This suggests that incorporating the five style-factor variables leads to a more accurate understanding of the data and can aid in making more informed decisions.
